ent of WordPress 5.0 with Gutenberg for Dec 6th: I&#8217;m with Yoast;<a href=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Selection_102.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-10767 aligncenter\" src=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Selection_102-300x148.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"148\" srcset=\"http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Selection_102-300x148.jpg 300w, http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Selection_102-624x308.jpg 624w, http://blog.futtta.be/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Selection_102.jpg 1022w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>He has a great &#8220;should I update&#8221;-checklist and conclusion in <a href=\"https://yoast.com/should-you-update-to-wordpress-5-0/\">this blogpost</a>;</p>\n<blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>Is <em>now</em> the right time to update?</li>\n<li>Can your site work with Gutenberg?</li>\n<li>Do you need it?</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>So our advice boils down to: if you <em>can</em> wait, wait. </strong></p></blockquote>\n<p>So if you have a busy end-of-year, if you&#8217;re not 100% sure your site will work with Gutenburg or if you don&#8217;t really need Gutenberg in the first place; wait (while WordPress 5.0 stabilizes with some minor releases).</p>\n<div class=\'yarpp-related-rss\'>\n<p>Possibly related twitterless twaddle:<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2018/01/23/of-bugs-inconsistencies-and-tag-soup-in-future-core/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Of bugs, inconsistencies and tag soup in (future) core\">Of bugs, inconsistencies and tag soup in (future) core </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2013/10/21/do-not-donate-to-me/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"Do not donate to me!\">Do not donate to me! </a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://blog.futtta.be/2015/01/27/wp-youtube-lyte-and-youtube-api-v2-end-of-life/\" rel=\"bookmark\" title=\"WP YouTube Lyte and YouTube API v2 end of life\">WP YouTube Lyte and YouTube API v2 end of life </a></li>\n</ul></p>\n</div>\n<